WEBVTT

00:10.570 --> 00:13.073
(Anya Marina's
"High on the Ceiling" plays)

00:20.120 --> 00:22.111
*

00:29.790 --> 00:32.054
Please, right here.

00:36.430 --> 00:39.467
* I read all your mail

00:40.670 --> 00:43.639
* I searched all your clothes

00:43.670 --> 00:47.777
* And I had you tracked

00:47.810 --> 00:51.701
* When you left home

00:51.750 --> 00:53.115
Here.

00:53.150 --> 00:57.484
* I watched all your tapes

00:57.520 --> 01:00.785
* Went through
all your magazines... *

01:02.830 --> 01:04.786
(clears throat)

01:04.830 --> 01:06.821
(laughs softly)

01:09.730 --> 01:11.288
Well, we could do mime.

01:11.330 --> 01:13.560
(laughs)

01:13.600 --> 01:15.591
Uh, they can't take
all of us, can they?

01:15.640 --> 01:18.268
No. Five percent.

01:18.310 --> 01:20.369
Any, uh, suggestions

01:20.410 --> 01:21.331
for getting out of jury duty?

01:21.380 --> 01:23.245
Yeah. Tell them you're a lawyer.

01:23.280 --> 01:24.178
Oh, do I have to?

01:24.210 --> 01:26.314
I'm Daniel by the way.

01:26.350 --> 01:28.409
Alicia.

01:28.450 --> 01:31.146
So, what do you do, Alicia?

01:31.190 --> 01:32.509
I'm a lawyer.

01:32.560 --> 01:34.255
Oops.

01:35.720 --> 01:37.688
Bad experience with lavwers?

01:37.730 --> 01:39.857
Uh... ex-wife.
(cell phone rings)

01:39.900 --> 01:41.891
Uh, excuse me.
Yeah.

01:41.930 --> 01:43.420
Hello?
ELI: Where are you?

01:43.470 --> 01:45.768
You're not at work.
Nice to talk to you, too, Eli.

01:45.800 --> 01:47.199
I'm at jury duty. What's up?

01:47.240 --> 01:48.764
They put you on a jury?

01:48.800 --> 01:51.200
What's up, Eli?
You're friend Finn,

01:52.510 --> 01:53.579
he's losing.

01:53.610 --> 01:54.736
How can he be losing?

01:54.780 --> 01:56.600
The campaign hasn't
even started yet.

01:56.650 --> 01:58.402
Alicia, the campaign started
when Peter vouched for him.

01:58.450 --> 02:00.179
He needs to win.

02:00.220 --> 02:02.279
His competition Castro is
out there getting endorsements.

02:02.320 --> 02:03.719
People don't know who Finn is.

02:03.750 --> 02:05.149
Who's his campaign manager?

02:05.190 --> 02:06.282
He doesn't have one.
Well, he needs one.

02:06.320 --> 02:07.309
Coffee!

02:07.360 --> 02:09.282
(sighs)
I've set up...

02:09.330 --> 02:11.924
No! An interview with WEQT

02:11.960 --> 02:13.359
to introduce him.

02:13.400 --> 02:14.799
Talk to him, Alicia.

02:14.830 --> 02:17.219
Uh, no, thank you, Eli.
They're calling me in now.

02:17.270 --> 02:18.191
No one's calling you in.

02:18.230 --> 02:19.629
Here they are. Bye.

02:19.670 --> 02:22.662
(groans)

02:22.710 --> 02:24.462
(cell phone rings)
Finn.

02:24.510 --> 02:26.637
This is Eli Gold calling
from the governor's office.

02:26.680 --> 02:28.568
Yes, Mr. Gold, hello.

02:28.610 --> 02:30.202
Look, I'm a little busy.

02:30.250 --> 02:31.877
I set up an interview
for today.

02:31.910 --> 02:34.276
A local station, WEQT,
at 6:00 pm.

02:34.320 --> 02:36.345
Excuse me_?
You're running
for state's attorney.

02:36.390 --> 02:38.346
I set up a TV interview.

02:38.390 --> 02:39.880
Be ready at 2:00.

02:39.920 --> 02:41.478
You said 6:00.
The interview's at 6:00.

02:41.520 --> 02:42.748
My prep is at 2:00.

02:42.790 --> 02:44.280
It'll take an hour.
Come by my office...

02:44.330 --> 02:45.649
I'll call you back.

02:45.690 --> 02:47.328
Ms. Lockhart?

02:47.360 --> 02:48.588
Uh, Finn Polmar.

02:48.630 --> 02:50.791
Oh, yes.
So, where can we do this?

02:50.830 --> 02:53.264
Where can_ we...?
The questioning.

02:53.300 --> 02:54.631
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

02:54.670 --> 02:55.739
Your firm invited us
to conduct

02:55.770 --> 02:56.862
the Pollard questioning here.

02:56.910 --> 02:58.332
So we're here.

02:58.370 --> 02:59.837
I, uh, I...

02:59.880 --> 03:01.939
Could you give me one second?

03:04.280 --> 03:05.907
Actually, uh, come with me.

03:05.950 --> 03:07.770
Please.

03:07.820 --> 03:10.709
(indistinct radio transmission)

03:10.750 --> 03:11.717
Good morning.
Good morning.

03:11.750 --> 03:12.557
I have an ASA

03:12.590 --> 03:14.512
and three policeman
waiting for me?

03:14.560 --> 03:16.619
Oh, yeah, that would
be for the Pollards.

03:16.660 --> 03:18.457
Lyle Pollard?

03:18.490 --> 03:19.957
He called this morning.
He said that, uh,

03:20.000 --> 03:21.797
that the police
were at his home,

03:21.830 --> 03:23.263
wanted to speak to his grandson.

03:23.300 --> 03:24.892
Kid was out,
so I suggested

03:24.930 --> 03:27.398
he tell them to meet here, and
we'd supervise the questioning.

03:27.440 --> 03:28.429
Regarding?

03:28.470 --> 03:29.505
What?
The-the questions

03:29.540 --> 03:30.905
are regarding...?

03:30.940 --> 03:32.476
Oh, uh, I have no idea.

03:35.880 --> 03:36.972
Mr. Canning.

03:37.010 --> 03:38.773
Why are you talking
to my clients?

03:38.810 --> 03:41.711
Well, your assistant
couldn't find you this morning.

03:41.750 --> 03:44.685
Uh, and she said it was
an important client.

03:44.720 --> 03:46.449
So I just took it.

03:46.490 --> 03:48.958
I mean, next time I won't
if you don't want me to.

03:48.990 --> 03:50.855
Let me think about that.

03:50.890 --> 03:52.448
WOMAN:
Juror 68?

03:52.500 --> 03:54.354
You are excused,
also Juror 72...

03:54.400 --> 03:55.389
You look familiar, Alicia.

03:55.430 --> 03:56.624
Why do you look familiar?

03:56.670 --> 03:59.298
I don't know. I have
one of those faces.

03:59.340 --> 04:02.434
_ MAN:
First row up.
Fill the empty seats, please.

04:02.470 --> 04:03.437
(sighs)

04:03.470 --> 04:05.938
Could I get in trouble
ifI said I was a lawyer?

04:05.970 --> 04:07.801
Uh, if you're lying, you will.

04:07.840 --> 04:09.649
Oh, so probably shouldn't.

04:09.680 --> 04:11.443
Depends on your taste
for adventure.

04:11.480 --> 04:12.879
MAN:
No cell phone use.

04:12.920 --> 04:14.342
(elevator bell dings)

04:14.380 --> 04:16.848
Oh, Diane, thank God!

04:16.890 --> 04:18.039
Is he here?

04:18.090 --> 04:20.308
Robbie? No, not yet.
What happened?

04:20.360 --> 04:21.782
They say he's selling pot.

04:21.820 --> 04:24.482
Can you believe
Robbie's selling pot?

04:24.530 --> 04:26.350
Do you know why all the police?
Yeah, sure.

04:26.400 --> 04:27.799
You know why.

04:27.830 --> 04:28.990
They're still after me

04:29.030 --> 04:31.328
for the work I did
in the '68 convention.

04:31.370 --> 04:33.361
They drive by the
house every day.

04:33.400 --> 04:34.628
Oh, here he is. Robbie.

04:34.670 --> 04:36.501
Don't worry, I just
went to the bathroom.

04:36.540 --> 04:37.564
What's up?

04:37.610 --> 04:39.601
We need to talk.

04:42.080 --> 04:43.809
DIANE:
Uh, just to be clear.

04:43.850 --> 04:46.546
I am allowing my client
to answer a limited number

04:46.580 --> 04:49.583
of questions to aid
your investigation

04:49.620 --> 04:51.747
as long as the conversation
is proffer-protected.

04:51.790 --> 04:54.611
It is. Thank you.

04:54.660 --> 04:56.651
Do you know
what Silk Road is, Robbie?

04:56.690 --> 04:57.850
A black market site?

04:57.890 --> 04:59.596
Yeah, it's a marketplace

04:59.630 --> 05:02.667
for the sale of drugs.

05:02.700 --> 05:05.419
Marijuana, cocaine, MDA,

05:05.470 --> 05:07.097
heroin, assault weapons

05:07.140 --> 05:10.405
and even murder.

05:10.440 --> 05:12.533
What Amazon is to book clubbers,

05:12.580 --> 05:15.378
Silk Road is to criminals.

05:15.410 --> 05:16.479
Have you ever logged into it?

05:16.510 --> 05:17.499
No.

05:17.550 --> 05:19.370
Not even to peruse it?

05:19.420 --> 05:21.012
He already said no!
Well, $1.2 billion

05:21.050 --> 05:24.440
in legal goods are bought
and sold on Silk Road.

05:24.490 --> 05:26.458
Now, that makes it
a class one felony

05:26.490 --> 05:28.515
for anyone involved
in running the site.

05:28.560 --> 05:30.380
I'm not hearing a
lot of questions,

05:30.430 --> 05:31.385
Mr. Polmar.

05:31.430 --> 05:33.921
We traced money

05:33.960 --> 05:35.518
from Silk Road
to your computer, Robbie.

05:35.560 --> 05:37.391
You traced money? What money?

05:37.430 --> 05:40.433
65 Bitcoin
worth approximately $39,000.

05:40.470 --> 05:43.735
We found it deposited
in Robbie's digital wallet.

05:43.770 --> 05:46.409
I've never bought anything
or sold anything on Silk Road.

05:46.440 --> 05:47.600
The money that we traced

05:47.640 --> 05:50.575
was to an employee.

05:50.610 --> 05:53.477
You're an employee of Silk Road.

05:53.520 --> 05:54.771
LYLE:
Robbie's in college.

05:54.820 --> 05:56.071
He's graduating in May.

05:56.120 --> 05:57.678
He's writing his thesis
for God's sake.

05:57.720 --> 06:00.518
We've worked with Bitcoin
before, Mr. Polmar.

06:00.560 --> 06:02.551
It's an anonymous currency.

06:02.590 --> 06:04.455
You can't trace it.
Oh, you couldn't.

06:04.490 --> 06:05.923
Until Mt. Gox was bankrupted.

06:05.960 --> 06:07.598
The Bitcoin exchange.

06:07.630 --> 06:09.495
Then law enforcement
was suddenly allowed

06:09.530 --> 06:11.623
access to the servers,
which meant that we could trace

06:11.670 --> 06:13.558
the Bitcoin to
Robbie's computer.

06:13.600 --> 06:15.431
Now, a class one
felony, Robbie?

06:15.470 --> 06:16.607
Four years

06:16.640 --> 06:18.767
to 15 years in prison.

06:18.810 --> 06:19.970
Mr. Polmar,
let's talk in private.

06:20.010 --> 06:22.478
Shall we?
Yeah.

06:26.780 --> 06:29.487
Mr. Canning,
do you have a minute?

06:33.020 --> 06:35.784
Why aren't you
arresting him?

06:35.820 --> 06:38.152
I want to know
what he knows.

06:38.190 --> 06:39.748
So, you're looking
for a plea?

06:39.800 --> 06:40.926
Yeah.

06:40.960 --> 06:42.791
Yeah, one year of jail time
for getting us

06:42.830 --> 06:46.630
to the top dog at Silk Road.

06:46.670 --> 06:49.559
And yet, you're
questioning him here

06:49.610 --> 06:50.804
and not at_ the
police station?

06:50.840 --> 06:52.000
That's true.

06:52.040 --> 06:54.008
You didn't want to be
seen strong-arming

06:54.040 --> 06:56.201
a kid with cerebral palsy?

06:56.240 --> 06:58.743
Oh, come on.
Especially one who was
an attorney like...

06:58.780 --> 07:00.008
Louis Canning.

07:00.050 --> 07:02.177
Hello, I'm Louis Canning.

07:02.220 --> 07:03.847
Nice to meet you.

07:03.890 --> 07:05.517
Uh, this is
ASA Polmar.

07:05.550 --> 07:07.814
Uh, why don't you, uh,

07:07.860 --> 07:10.454
describe your disorder,
Mr. Canning?

07:11.560 --> 07:13.050
Yeah, it's, uh,
tardive dyskinesia.

07:13.100 --> 07:14.499
It's a neurological disorder...

07:14.530 --> 07:16.623
Which plays
well on camera.

07:16.670 --> 07:18.626
Especially if he has
a client with cerebral palsy.

07:18.670 --> 07:20.490
Your client's involved
In one of the biggest

07:20.540 --> 07:21.996
criminal conspiracies
of the let century.

07:22.040 --> 07:24.463
All you have is a few Bitcoin...

07:24.510 --> 07:26.159
And you're running for
state's attorney, aren't you?

07:26.210 --> 07:27.632
POLMAR:
What does that have
to do with this?

07:27.680 --> 07:29.079
Well, you wouldn't want
to be seen

07:29.110 --> 07:30.805
falsely accusing
another young man.

07:30.850 --> 07:31.908
Especially since

07:31.950 --> 07:33.577
your last wrongful prosecution

07:33.620 --> 07:35.713
resulted in the death
of an attorney

07:35.750 --> 07:37.081
and a witness.

07:41.520 --> 07:43.249
I have a witness.

07:43.290 --> 07:44.826
To what?
Your client

07:44.860 --> 07:46.225
participating in Silk Road.

07:46.260 --> 07:48.956
But you have another problem.

07:49.000 --> 07:51.025
Lyle Pollard.

07:51.070 --> 07:52.867
He's one of your richest
clients, isn't he?

07:52.900 --> 07:55.664
Well, Robbie worked on Silk Road
in his grandfather's basement.

07:55.700 --> 07:58.498
That means that I can freeze
his grandfather's assets.

08:02.080 --> 08:04.640
Juror 499, please
state your name.

08:04.680 --> 08:06.739
Uh, Daniel Irwin.
And your occupation.

08:08.750 --> 08:11.685
I-I design batteries.

08:11.720 --> 08:12.789
What does that entail?

08:12.820 --> 08:14.617
Uh, well, I'm, uh,

08:14.660 --> 08:16.082
I'm working
on a lithium ion battery

08:16.120 --> 08:19.226
that's 2,000 times more powerful
than current batteries.

08:19.260 --> 08:21.626
_ It's for use_
In computers and In cars.

08:21.660 --> 08:22.422
That's very impressive.

08:22.460 --> 08:23.324
Do you think
that you could judge

08:23.370 --> 08:25.895
_ this case _
of Indecent exposure faIrly?

08:25.930 --> 08:27.136
I-I don't, uh, know.

08:27.170 --> 08:29.730
I have friends who...
friends who are lavwers,

08:29.770 --> 08:32.307
and that might influence me.

08:32.340 --> 08:35.207
The Defense has no objections
to this juror,

08:35.240 --> 08:36.901
Your Honor.

08:36.950 --> 08:39.714
Juror 503,
please state your name.

08:39.750 --> 08:42.218
Alicia Florrick.

08:42.250 --> 08:43.945
I see. Uh, you are
the governor's wife.

08:43.990 --> 08:45.218
Iam.

08:45.250 --> 08:46.649
And you're a lawyer.

08:46.690 --> 08:47.679
Yes.

08:47.720 --> 08:49.620
Well, it was very nice
to meet you, Mrs. Florrick.

08:49.660 --> 08:51.685
Uh, the Defense would like

08:51.730 --> 08:53.721
_ to exercise
Its preemptory challenge.

08:53.760 --> 08:55.227
MAN:
Okay, the juror is excused.
Thank you.

08:55.260 --> 08:56.921
Well, it was
very nice to meet you.

08:56.970 --> 08:58.619
Well, next time
I'll say I'm a lawyer.

08:58.670 --> 09:00.661
Good luck.

09:02.670 --> 09:04.638
That's it, I'm done.

09:04.670 --> 09:06.331
No more jury duty.

09:06.370 --> 09:08.201
Ah, that was easy.
Yeah.

09:08.240 --> 09:09.605
I'm coming in.
I'll see you in a few minutes.

09:09.650 --> 09:11.675
Nope.
What do you mean?

09:11.710 --> 09:13.610
You're not coming in.
How am I not coming in?

09:16.650 --> 09:18.140
(laughs)
Cary, thanks.

09:18.190 --> 09:20.750
ButI have a lot...
No, you don't.

09:20.790 --> 09:21.916
Seriously, how many days
have you had off

09:21.960 --> 09:23.188
in the last five years?

09:23.230 --> 09:25.255
I don't know.

09:25.290 --> 09:26.359
I do.

09:26.390 --> 09:27.755
The same as me-- none.

09:27.800 --> 09:29.597
So today is your day off.

09:29.630 --> 09:30.961
This is my gift to you.

09:31.000 --> 09:32.638
Take it.

09:32.670 --> 09:33.796
(sighs)

09:33.840 --> 09:35.990
Thanks, Cary.
You're a good man.

09:36.040 --> 09:37.701
Nah, I'm a good partner.

09:37.740 --> 09:39.105
Okay, I'm taking the day off.

09:39.140 --> 09:41.279
This is me taking
the day off.

09:41.310 --> 09:43.005
I didn't do it.

09:43.050 --> 09:44.074
DIANE:
I know,

09:44.110 --> 09:46.613
but how did this Bitcoin end up

09:46.650 --> 09:47.617
on your computer?

09:47.650 --> 09:49.311
They use zombie computers.
Maybe it was that?

09:49.350 --> 09:50.715
He's been busy

09:50.750 --> 09:52.012
doing his graduate work.
He's had no time...

09:52.050 --> 09:53.381
Lyle, could you
give us a minute?

09:53.420 --> 09:54.614
W-W-What do you mean?

09:54.660 --> 09:55.786
Could you step out
for a minute?

09:55.820 --> 09:56.718
Why?!

09:56.760 --> 09:57.829
I'll come and get you.
Please?

10:04.870 --> 10:07.839
They say they have
a witness, Robbie.

10:07.870 --> 10:09.360
How could they have a witness?

10:14.940 --> 10:17.738
Lyle, wait in reception, please.

10:17.780 --> 10:18.747
He's innocent.

10:18.780 --> 10:19.815
This is about the cops.

10:19.850 --> 10:21.249
I know. Reception.

10:22.790 --> 10:23.745
Kalinda, do you have a minute?

10:23.790 --> 10:24.609
Sure.

10:24.650 --> 10:27.813
CANNING:
Look, everybody wants to rebel.

10:27.860 --> 10:30.829
I mean, for me in-in college

10:30.860 --> 10:32.748
it-it was girls.

10:32.800 --> 10:34.859
The key is to not let it affect

10:34.900 --> 10:36.925
the rest of your life.

10:36.970 --> 10:38.790
Everybody wants a clean slate.

10:38.830 --> 10:40.889
This is a chance
to make this yours.

10:40.940 --> 10:42.191
So, tell us.

10:42.240 --> 10:44.663
We-we'll find a way
to tell your grandfather.

10:44.710 --> 10:45.859
He will understand.

10:45.910 --> 10:47.309
Believe me, I promise you.

10:52.280 --> 10:53.816
I wrote reviews for them.

10:53.850 --> 10:56.341
For Silk Road?

10:56.380 --> 10:59.087
Yeah.

10:59.120 --> 11:01.816
They wanted some business.

11:01.860 --> 11:04.454
They paid me
to write client reviews

11:04.490 --> 11:05.889
to get more sales moving.

11:05.930 --> 11:07.227
Right. But you didn't sample
the product.

11:07.260 --> 11:09.455
No, they-they weren't
real reviews.

11:09.500 --> 11:10.319
They were just planted.

11:10.370 --> 11:14.739
You know, "great high,
fast delivery."

11:14.770 --> 11:18.262
I created a ratings system
for the quality of the high:

11:18.310 --> 11:20.904
"Five William S. Burroughs."

11:20.940 --> 11:22.771
It was all a joke.
That's what

11:22.810 --> 11:23.902
you were paid for?

11:23.950 --> 11:25.076
Yeah.

11:25.110 --> 11:26.407
(sighs)
What?

11:26.450 --> 11:28.372
I never did anything.
I just wrote reviews.

11:28.420 --> 11:33.187
But you abetted $1.2 billion
in drug sales.

11:33.220 --> 11:34.778
It makes you
an accessory.

11:34.820 --> 11:36.185
KALIN DA:
Who paid you?

11:36.220 --> 11:37.881
Uh, this is
our investigator.

11:37.930 --> 11:39.727
Hi.

11:39.760 --> 11:40.829
I don't know.

11:40.860 --> 11:42.259
It was all done anonymously.

11:42.300 --> 11:44.860
They say they have a witness,
Robbie.

11:44.900 --> 11:46.128
Who can that be?

11:46.170 --> 11:47.467
I don't know.

11:49.140 --> 11:50.937
What?

11:50.970 --> 11:53.768
There was this girl.

11:53.810 --> 11:56.404
I was just talking
to her near school.

11:57.480 --> 11:59.107
I offered to write her a review

11:59.150 --> 12:01.846
if she ever got on Silk Road
to sell anything.

12:01.880 --> 12:04.110
And what was her name?

12:04.150 --> 12:08.780
Hi, uh, Corsica.
Sorry to interrupt you.

12:08.820 --> 12:11.152
Yeah, come on in.
I've got two new types.

12:11.190 --> 12:13.055
Northern Lights,
8-52 on the coffee table.

12:13.100 --> 12:14.328
Nice.

12:14.360 --> 12:16.351
Yeah, uh-huh.

12:17.870 --> 12:20.532
No, not tonight.
But look, someone's here.

12:20.570 --> 12:22.458
I'll call you back, okay?

12:24.870 --> 12:26.360
So, what are you looking for?

12:26.410 --> 12:27.877
Actually,

12:27.910 --> 12:29.901
I'm looking for information
on Robbie Pollard.

12:31.810 --> 12:33.869
I have nothing to say.

12:33.920 --> 12:34.716
I think you already had

12:34.750 --> 12:36.217
something to say...
to the police.

12:37.420 --> 12:39.081
_ You're not
In any danger.

