I'm referring the Pollards

40:12.010 --> 40:12.999
to another law firm.

40:13.040 --> 40:14.473
Thanks for coming over here.

40:24.150 --> 40:25.082
Hey, Alicia.

40:25.120 --> 40:26.087
You got a minute?

40:26.120 --> 40:28.088
I do. How are you doing?

40:28.120 --> 40:30.918
Oh, it's been a long day.

40:30.960 --> 40:32.188
Here, too.

40:32.230 --> 40:33.754
Look, I'm on a case.

40:33.790 --> 40:35.997
Lockhart/Gardner's
on the other side.

40:36.030 --> 40:37.156
Or was.

40:37.200 --> 40:38.189
Diane just withdrew herself

40:38.230 --> 40:40.198
from the case for no reason.

40:40.230 --> 40:41.162
Now, is that like her?

40:41.200 --> 40:42.462
Well...

40:42.500 --> 40:44.195
Do you feel comfortable
discussing this?

40:44.240 --> 40:46.128
Yes. I...
It's not like her.

40:46.170 --> 40:48.934
The clients are her friends,
the Pollards.

40:48.980 --> 40:50.231
Oh, I know them.

40:50.280 --> 40:51.679
The grandson.

40:51.710 --> 40:53.473
No, I don't know him.

40:53.510 --> 40:56.115
Is there a chance the client
Intends to perjure hImself?

40:56.150 --> 40:58.141
Well, I can't say
for certain, but

40:58.180 --> 41:00.580
it would be one reason why
Diane would back out.

41:00.620 --> 41:02.053
She would never suborn perjury.

41:05.090 --> 41:06.580
Okay. Thanks.

41:06.630 --> 41:08.723
Hey... sounds like
you're on the street.

41:08.760 --> 41:09.897
You all right?

41:09.930 --> 41:12.262
I had the... had a day off.

41:12.300 --> 41:13.927
Sounds good.

41:13.970 --> 41:15.892
Uh, did Eli get ahold of you?

41:15.940 --> 41:17.567
Yeah.

41:17.600 --> 41:20.068
Yeah...

41:20.110 --> 41:21.737
He wants to turn me
Into a hero.

41:21.780 --> 41:23.179
Yes.

41:23.210 --> 41:24.700
Eli is good at that.

41:24.750 --> 41:26.069
That's right.

41:26.110 --> 41:27.805
He already turned you
into a saint.

41:27.850 --> 41:29.545
Yep.

41:29.580 --> 41:30.945
Talk to you later.

41:32.690 --> 41:33.816
This is a betrayal.

41:33.850 --> 41:34.987
It's better for Robbie
that I do.

41:38.090 --> 41:39.626
How can you just withdraw?

41:39.660 --> 41:41.252
It's best for
Robbie that I do.

41:41.290 --> 41:43.258
Why? Tell me why.

41:43.300 --> 41:44.927
I can't.

41:44.970 --> 41:46.790
Diane, you're abandoning us.

41:46.830 --> 41:47.797
My apologies.

41:47.830 --> 41:48.831
Oh, thank you!

41:48.870 --> 41:50.189
That-that's very helpful.

41:58.710 --> 42:00.143
Sounded like it went poorly.

42:00.180 --> 42:03.149
Not great.

42:03.180 --> 42:04.272
Do you have
something?

42:04.320 --> 42:05.719
Yeah.

42:05.750 --> 42:06.978
On Canning?

42:07.020 --> 42:08.248
Yes.

42:08.290 --> 42:09.917
So is he dying?

42:09.960 --> 42:11.188
Or is he trying
to screw me?

42:13.330 --> 42:16.299
He is dying...

42:16.330 --> 42:18.218
and he's trying to screw you.

42:18.260 --> 42:20.262
(Anya Marina's
"High on the Ceiling" plays)

42:47.360 --> 42:49.225
It's one drink.

42:49.260 --> 42:50.693
Why is that a problem?

42:53.400 --> 42:55.368
Who am I being faithful to?

